name: Evgenii Kniazev
headline: AI & Software Architect | Agentic Engineer | Inventor
creator: True
school_1: Carnegie Mellon University - Software Engineering Institute
bio:
Evgenii is an Engineer of Agentic systems who applies his expertise in Enterprise software engineering for regulated domains including medical, transportation and finance to transform companies to become AI first companies.

Evgenii serves as a computer science expert contributing to OpenAI within HumanData team projects.

Evgenii helped to transform SODA.Auto automotive startup to leverage software agents to tackle specification, code and test generation for 4x speed up of development.

Evgenii Helped to create Invisalign Go product line by reaching 99%+ automation in medical device space.

Evgenii Co-founded VisualSVN with 1M+ users.

As PhD in Machine Learning on Software Repositories and senior engineer at Meta, helped to automatically minimize code and data to improve privacy of the products used by billions of people.

In 2021 Evgenii endorsed by TechNation as a Global Talent.

name: Simon C.
headline: Founding Partner @ Stanley Capital | Private Equity, MBA
creator: False
bio:
Simon is a founding partner at Stanley Capital which he started in 2018 initially as Stanley Capital Limited which was a consulting firm that then executed two independent sponsor investments with Simon originating both and co-lead on execution on one and lead on another. 

Stanley Capital Partners LLP is now a European mid-market private equity firm using a research and technology-based approach to identify opportunities in the growing sustainable investment sectors of Healthcare and tech enabled services. Stanley Capital targets businesses with the potential of generating EBITDA of $25m to $150m. We partner with management teams, in majority and minority transactions, to transform and grow companies through technological change, operational change and market consolidation. 
 
With over 16 years of direct PE experience, Simon has led 12 platform buy out investments, 50+ bolt-on acquisitions, including 3 mergers and one carve out. Simon served as an IC member and Managing Director at Ardian's Buyout team and was a Director at HgCapital prior to founding SCP in 2018. Simon currently has a 3.5x CoC average fully attributed and realised track record and 2.7x weighted. 

Simon has successfully originated, led or co-led the buyouts at HgCapital of Parts Alliance (2.0x), GSF (2.0x), Zenith (2.9x) and Leasedrive (2.9x); at Ardian of Envision Pharma (2.4x) and Trigo (2.4x unrealised); as an independent sponsor of Essential Pharma (3.3x - SC with Gyrus Capital), Noden Pharma (6.7x) and at Stanley Capital of Qinecsa Solutions, Laboratoire XO (unrealised), Arietta.AI (37x) and Roboyo (unrealised).

Simon holds an MBA from INSEAD, an MA and a Richard Blackwell Scholarship from Oxford University,  2 Oriel College academic prizes and was one of 3 top Scholars at Shrewsbury School. Simon is an Olympian being a GB Olympic semi finalist oarsman in Athens in 2004. Simon made Partner from Associate in 7 years and was in the inaugural 40 under 40 PE News list.

bio:
🚀 Founder | 🌱 Climate Tech Innovator | 💡 AI/ML Expert | 🎯 Product Visionary

Driving innovation at the intersection of technology and sustainability. With 18+ years of experience building transformative solutions, I'm passionate about leveraging cutting-edge technology to solve some of the world's most pressing challenges.

🏆 Recognition & Achievements:
• Techstars Sustainability Paris Cohort Member
• Top 10 AI/ML Startups - GSK Vaccine Innovation Summit
• Barclays Eagle Labs

💪 What Drives Me:
I believe in building technology that matters. From developing sustainable climate tech platforms to fintech solutions,my focus is on innovations that drive meaningful impact. My ventures have consistently pushed boundaries in:
• Climate Tech & ESG Solutions
• Enterprise AI/ML Applications
• Financial Technology

🛠️ Innovation Track Record:
• Built and scaled multiple B2B platforms using advanced AI/ML
• Developed breakthrough solutions for  GSK, Ford Mobility,CLS FX Group
• Pioneered ESG-focused technology solutions

🌐 Global Impact:
Leading teams across continents, I've worked with organizations ranging from Fortune 500 companies to innovative startups. My solutions have been implemented across BFSI, Healthcare, Automotive, and Public Sector industries.

🤝 Looking to Connect With:
• Fellow entrepreneurs and innovators
• Sustainability and climate tech enthusiasts
• AI/ML experts and technologists
• Impact investors and VCs
• Corporate innovation leaders

📈 Recent Focus:
• Sustainable Technology Solutions
• AI-Driven Enterprise Platforms
• ESG Innovation
• Financial Inclusion

"Innovation is not just about technology; it's about creating solutions that make a difference in people's lives."

Let's connect and explore how we can create meaningful impact together. Open to discussions about:
• Partnership opportunities
• Advisory roles
• Speaking engagements
• Investment opportunities
• Innovation collaboration

name: Marc Montanari
headline: Solutions @ OpenAI | Co-host @ The Data Coffee Break Podcast
creator: True
school_2: EBS Universität für Wirtschaft und Recht
bio:
Solution Engineer and manager with experience in data observability, business intelligence, data analysis, data engineering, cloud solution architecture and data warehousing. I lead pre-sales conversations from business users to C-level across a wide range of industries in the Commercial and Enterprise space.

Worked extensively across diverse markets: France, UK, Southern Europe, Mediterranean, Middle East and Africa.

Holds two Master's degrees: Master of Engineering (M.Eng.) focused in Industrial Processes from ESIAB (France) and Master of Science (MSc.) focused in Management Finance from Durham University Business School (UK).

Outside work, I'm a self-taught equity crowdfunding investor.

name: Henry Scott-Green
headline: Product @ OpenAI | ex Co-Founder/CEO at Context.ai (joined OpenAI)
creator: True
bio:
Building evals at OpenAI 

Previously Co-Founder/CEO at Context.ai, where we built evals and analytics for LLMs. We joined OpenAI in April 2025. Our product was relied on by enterprises including Unilever, Klarna, Cisco, Hasbro, Algolia, and Delivery Hero. We raised $3.5M from Google Ventures, Theory Ventures, and unicorn founder angel investors.

I spent 7 years as a Product Manager at Google, building 4 zero-to-one YouTube monetization tools from launch to $750M ARR. I worked at multi-billion user scale, completed Google's APM program, and hold 4 patents across AI and anti-abuse.

I founded a medical research nonprofit for Long Covid that raised $17M and graduated with a Computer Science degree from UCL.

headline: I advised 400+ founders 🙏🏼 Kindness is my strategy - Senior Advisor and Venture Partner to VCs and PEs | NED | Venture Capitalist | 4X Founder | Built 2XCVCs | Keynote Speaker (illaigescheit.com) | Linkedin Top Voice
creator: True
past_company_2: 🌏 The Atlas Capital & Climate Tech Coalition
bio:
Here you can work with me: 
- Book your Executive Coaching session: https://www.illaigescheit.com/workwithme
- Apply to the Gescheit & Partners Venture Equity Program: https://www.illaigescheit.com/equity-program
- Invite Illai to speak: https://www.illaigescheit.com/
- Explore workshops on Fundraising with AI: https://www.illaigescheit.com/fundraising-with-ai-1
- Reading is a super power for me - here you can find my favourite books and my next reads: https://www.illaigescheit.com/my-book-list-1

About me: 
Illai is a serial entrepreneur, board advisor and investor. He spends his career building venture funds, businesses and working with entrepreneurs in diverse areas such as enterprise and consumer software and climate technologies. Illai is a Founding Partner of Gescheit & Partners, a strategy and innovation advisory firm and serves on advisory boards of funds such as Atlas Capital and Barka Fund. He was a Venture Partner at Siemens Energy Ventures and previously served as Entrepreneur-in-Residence at BP. He built and scaled new venturing units focused on decarbonization, energy and climate tech and helped build their portfolio of next generation sustainability and technology startups. Illai is an inventor of over 20 patents and his early entrepreneurial story was featured in the Harvard-MIT book publication Entrepreneurial Negotiation. He is a member of the Ashoka Entrepreneur-to-Entrepreneur Network, member of the Expert Network for the World Economic Forum and a Guest Lecturer at London Business School. 

My Motto: "Focus on hiring Heartcounts, not Headcounts"

My Leadership principles: 
1. Empower and Inspire. 
2. Generosity and Curiosity. 
3. Humility and Respect. 
4. Compassionate and Human.
